//  Request / Response / Testing / Routing in ExpressJS

1. npm init -y                 = for creating package.json
2. npm install express         = for node modules
3. npm install nodemon         = for automatically reset (means hame br br code change krne pr,apne application ko restart krn pad raha tha, khud se restart ho jaye , uske liye iska use hota h )
4. npm run dev                 = krne p basic backend application badhiya chal rhi hame


1. How many types of Request recive on server :-
i) GET        = for data fetch krne ke liye.Most of the time iska use hi hota h.
ii) POST       = bhut sara data kahi p save krwana chahte h, kahi par , kch new entry create krna chahte h, kahi par to waha p post Request k use kr rhe hote h.
iii) PUT       = jo already exisiting items h, uska update krna chahta h, to waha p put Request k aap use kr rhe hote h.
iv) DELETE     = exisiting item ko delete krn chhahte ho to, iska use krte h.


2. Postman ka use kyun karte hain?

API sahi kaam kar rahi hai ya nahi
✔ Data bhej rahe (POST)
✔ Data la rahe (GET)
✔ Data update (PUT/PATCH)
✔ Data delete (DELETE)
✔ Token / Auth test karna
✔ Error dekhna (400, 500 etc)

3. Browser me sirf GET check hota
But Postman se tum:
GET
POST
PUT
DELETE
sab check kar sakti ho 


request ki kahani

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  // res.send("got a GET request");
  // res.sendFile(__dirname + '/dummy.html');
  res.endFile(__dirname + '/index.html');
});

app.post('/items', (req,res) => {
  // res.send("got a POST request");
  res.json({x:1, y:2,  });
})

app.put('/items/:id', (req,res) => {
  res.send("got a PUT request");
})

app.delete('/items/:id', (req,res) => {
  res.send("got a DELETE request");
})